美国官方<ref>{{Cite web|title=UNITED STATES ARMY IN THE KOREAN WAR TRUCE TENT AND FIGHTING FRONT|url=https://history.army.mil/books/korea/truce/fm.htm|accessdate=|author=Walter G. Hermes|date=1965|format=|publisher=|language=|archive-date=2021-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206083909/https://history.army.mil/books/korea/truce/fm.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>和学界普遍认为是朝鲜对韩国主动发起战争，部分学者如Hugh Deane<ref>{{Cite book|chapter=|url=https://books.google.co.jp/books?id=XMJpnYmKNQsC&pg=PA86&lpg=PA86&dq=haeju+Korean+war&source=bl&ots=MPbyahDzgo&sig=ACfU3U22lr88GD9q3RfwQ-Z3f8G_me-OGw&hl=zh-CN&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=haeju%20Korean%20war&f=false|publisher=China Books|date=1999|isbn=978-0-8351-2644-1|language=en|first=Hugh|last=Deane|title=The Korean War 1945-1953|year=|location=|pages=|access-date=2021-02-01|archive-date=2021-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206125438/https://books.google.co.jp/books?id=XMJpnYmKNQsC&pg=PA86&lpg=PA86&dq=haeju+Korean+war&source=bl&ots=MPbyahDzgo&sig=ACfU3U22lr88GD9q3RfwQ-Z3f8G_me-OGw&hl=zh-CN&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=haeju%20Korean%20war&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Setting the Record Straight on the Korean War|url=https://monthlyreview.org/2000/10/01/setting-the-record-straight-on-the-korean-war/|accessdate=|author=Martin Hart-Landsberg|date=2000-10-01|format=|publisher=MONTHLY REVIEW|language=|archive-date=2021-04-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210411045502/https://monthlyreview.org/2000/10/01/setting-the-record-straight-on-the-korean-war/|dead-url=no}}</ref>以及[[布魯斯·卡明斯|布魯斯·卡明斯]]<ref>{{Cite book|title=Korea's Place in the Sun : A Modern History.|last=Bruce|first=Cumings|publisher=W. W. Norton & Company|year=2005|isbn=978-0393327021|location=New York|page=pp.278-280}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title=Origins of the Korean War|last=Cumings|first=Bruce|publisher=Princeton University Press|year=1981|isbn=978-8976966124|location=|pages=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title=The Korean War: A History|url=https://archive.org/details/koreanwarhistory0000cumi|last=Cumings|first=Bruce|publisher=Modern library|year=2010|isbn=9780679603788|location=New York|pages=pp.53-55|quote=The fighting on Ongjin began around 3 or 4 A.M. on June 25; initial intelligence reports were inconclusive as to who started it. Later on, attacking elements were said to be from the 3rd Brigade of the Democratic People’s Republic of Korea (DPRK) Border Constabulary, joined at 5:30 A.M. by the formidable 6th Division. At about the same time, according to the American official history, KPA forces at the parallel south of Chorwon assaulted the 1st Regiment of the ROKA 7th Division, dealing it heavy casualties; it gave way and the 3rd and 4th KPA divisions, with an armored brigade, crashed through and began a daunting march toward Seoul. South Korean sources asserted, however, that elements of the 17th Regiment had counterattacked on the Ongjin Peninsula and were in possession of Haeju city, the only important point north of the 38th parallel claimed to have been taken by ROK forces.Roy Appleman, America’s official historian of the war, relied on James Hausman’s heavily sanitized account of the war’ s start on the Ongjin Peninsula. Hausman later told a Thames Television documentary crew that his good friend Paek In-yŏp (brother to Paek Sŏn-yŏp) was the commander on Ongjin, “and when the war broke out as you know he was there not only defending his line but counterattacking” (that is, across the parallel). As for “those who think that the South may have started this war,” Hausman went on, “I think … I think they’re wrong.” Another Thames interviewee, Col. James Peach, an Australian who was with the UN observer group, reported that the Ongjin commander, Paek, was “a get-going sort of chap” who led the “twin-tiger” 17th Regimental Combat Team: “I, I never quite knew what went on. There’s a bit of a mystery still about Haeju, I think it might have been Paek and his merry men, the 17th Regiment, attacking it … We didn’t hear anything about it until the war had been going for a while, and I never quite knew what went on. It’s been said that they attacked there and that the North Koreans responded.” Peach went on to say that he didn’t think this version held much water. (Note also that if the South Koreans attack, it is “Paek and his merry men”; when the North Koreans do the same, it is heinous aggression.) Whether 17th Regiment soldiers may have occupied Haeju on June 25, or even initiated the fighting on Ongjin, is still inconclusive, with the existing evidence pointing both ways. There is no evidence, however, to back up the North’s claim that the South launched a general invasion; at worst there may have been a small assault across the parallel, as happened many times in 1949. Whatever transpired, the North met it with a full invasion.}}</ref>等持有韩国先开战的观点。

印度学者Karunakar Gupta于1972年在文章"How Did the Korean War Begin?"中分析了韩国军队首先越界的可能性，但是没有有力的证据可以证明这一点。<ref name=":6" />随后美国学者[[李庭植|李庭植]]<ref name=":11">{{Cite journal|title=The Korean War: A Second Comment|url=https://www.jstor.org/stable/652007|last=Lee|first=Chong-sik|date=1973|journal=The China Quarterly|issue=54|pages=361–362|issn=0305-7410|access-date=2021-02-01|archive-date=2021-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206165259/https://www.jstor.org/stable/652007|dead-url=no}}</ref>,{{Link-en|Robert Simmons|Rob Simmons}}<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Some Myths about June 1950|url=https://www.jstor.org/stable/652006|last=Simmons|first=Robert R.|date=1973|journal=The China Quarterly|issue=54|pages=354–361|issn=0305-7410|access-date=2021-02-01|archive-date=2021-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206191426/https://www.jstor.org/stable/652006|dead-url=no}}</ref>均撰文反驳这一观点。"How Did the Korean War Begin?"与Karunakar Gupta在1974年的另一篇文章“The hidden history of the Sino-Indian frontier”<ref>{{Cite journal|title=The Hidden History of the Sino-Indian Frontier. By Karunakar Gupta. [Calcutta: Minerva, 1974. 176 pp. Rs. 30.00.]|url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/china-quarterly/article/abs/hidden-history-of-the-sinoindian-frontier-by-karunakar-gupta-calcutta-minerva-1974-176-pp-rs-3000/8E18DEC4521A202E30756B10C385BBAC|last=Lamb|first=Alastair|date=1976/06|journal=The China Quarterly|doi=10.1017/S0305741000033841|volume=66|pages=386–388|language=en|issn=1468-2648|access-date=2021-02-01|archive-date=2021-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210427045954/https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/china-quarterly/article/abs/hidden-history-of-the-sinoindian-frontier-by-karunakar-gupta-calcutta-minerva-1974-176-pp-rs-3000/8E18DEC4521A202E30756B10C385BBAC|dead-url=no}}</ref>部分内容有出入，后者将韩国陆军第1师师长错写为白仁烨。

韩国学者{{Link-ko|鄭秉峻|정병준}}教授认为由韩国先发制人进攻海州的行动并不存在，他认为，对海州的攻击是{{Link-ko|韩国陆军本部|대한민국_육군본부}}在1950年3月制定的“作战命令38号”下的正常防御计划的一部分，且陆军本部攻击海州的命令在1950年6月26日（[[UTC+09:00|UTC+09:00]]）而非6月25日（[[UTC+09:00|UTC+09:00]]）发出；且韩国宣称的海州反击战也不存在，因为6月25日上午在北韩军队[[甕津戰役|攻击]]后，驻守瓮津的韩国军队已经处于崩溃状态，不具备反攻的能力。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2006/06/23/2006062370649.html|title=“남침유도 해주점령說은 허구”|author=유석재|date=2006-06-23|work=|publisher=朝鮮日報|accessdate=|language=|format=|archive-date=2021-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206192711/https://www.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2006/06/23/2006062370649.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=“남침 유도 해주 진공설은 근거 없어” {{!}} DailyNK|url=https://www.dailynk.com/%eb%82%a8%ec%b9%a8-%ec%9c%a0%eb%8f%84-%ed%95%b4%ec%a3%bc-%ec%a7%84%ea%b3%b5%ec%84%a4%ec%9d%80-%ea%b7%bc%ea%b1%b0-%ec%97%86%ec%96%b4/|access-date=2021-10-05|last=DailyNK|language=ko|archive-date=2021-10-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211005030719/https://www.dailynk.com/%eb%82%a8%ec%b9%a8-%ec%9c%a0%eb%8f%84-%ed%95%b4%ec%a3%bc-%ec%a7%84%ea%b3%b5%ec%84%a4%ec%9d%80-%ea%b7%bc%ea%b1%b0-%ec%97%86%ec%96%b4/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

